Functional Specification Document (FSD)
Module: User Login
Application: XYZ Web Application
Version: 1.0
Date: 10-Nov-2025
Prepared by: [Your Name]
1. Purpose
The purpose of the Login Page is to authenticate users securely before granting access to the system. It validates user credentials against the registered user database.
2. Scope
This functionality allows users with valid credentials to log in to the application. Unauthorized users are prevented from accessing protected modules.
3. Functional Requirements
3.1 Login Page Elements
Field / Component	Type	Description	Validation / Rules
Username / Email	Text Input	Used to enter registered username or email	Mandatory; cannot be empty; should match registered record
Password	Password Input	Used to enter user password	Mandatory; cannot be empty; minimum 8 characters
Remember Me	Checkbox	Option to keep user logged in for next session	Optional
Login Button	Button	Submits entered credentials for authentication	Enabled only when both fields are filled
Forgot Password	Link	Redirects to password recovery screen	Active and clickable
Register Now	Link	Redirects to registration screen	Active and clickable
4. Functional Flow
Normal Flow:
1.	1. User navigates to the Login page.
2.	2. User enters valid Username/Email and Password.
3.	3. User clicks Login button.
4.	4. System sends credentials to backend API for validation.
5.	5. Backend verifies credentials in the database.
6.	6. If valid: System redirects user to Dashboard/Home Page and displays success message.
7.	7. If invalid: Displays error message and allows retry.
5. Error Handling
Error Condition	Message Displayed
Username field empty	Please enter your username.
Password field empty	Please enter your password.
Invalid credentials	Invalid username or password.
Server not reachable	Unable to connect. Please try again later.
6. Security Requirements
•	Password must not be stored or transmitted in plain text.
•	HTTPS protocol must be used for data transmission.
•	Implement rate limiting for failed login attempts.
•	Session tokens must expire after inactivity.
7. Acceptance Criteria
•	User should be able to login successfully with valid credentials.
•	Login button should remain disabled until all mandatory fields are filled.
•	Invalid credentials should trigger an error message.
•	Passwords should never be displayed in plain text.
•	After login, user should be redirected to Dashboard.
